author: cbc
title: RNC, RCMP officers to testify at Don Dunphy inquiry today
text:
The inquiry into the shooting death of Don Dunphy will resume today, with three police officers expected to provide testimony.
Insp. Pat Cahill of the Royal Canadian Mounted Police is scheduled to appear at 9:30 a.m., followed by Cpl. Kelly Lee, also of the RCMP.
Insp. Barry Constantine of the Royal Newfoundland Constabulary is also set to appear.
Follow updates from the inquiry in our live blog.
